Notes: For Persistence, Alexis Breen (Coder1) removed touches that Vincent Kiepsch (Coder2) scored that were NOT directed to the focal object (after clarifying this piece of the instructions with him)

GENERAL NOTE: for exploration and boldness, columns Coder1 and Coder2 were aligned according to latency and classification and NAs were inserted for the other coder when one coder coded more state changes in a particular section of the video (Alexis and Corina both did the aligning). This avoided inaccurate pairings of categories due to the wrong points of the video being compared to each other. For example, if Coder1 scored Near at second 238 and InTent at second 454, and coder 2 scored Near at second 237.6, then two more behaviors, then InTent at second 454, then two rows were added to the data sheet to account for Coder2's 2 extra behaviors and NAs were listed for Coder1 in these cells.
